<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54141e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54141e">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54141e"> 141(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> unlike image <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54141e"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Cette fa&ccedil;on de proc&eacute;der est instructive. Les indig&egrave;nes d&eacute;sirent savoir s&apos;il n&apos;est rien arriv&eacute; de f&acirc;cheux au visiteur ami qui est maintenant loin d&apos;eux, et ne peut leur donner de ses nouvelles. Ils y suppl&eacute;ent en &eacute;tablissant une participation entre lui et un symbole qui le &laquo;repr&eacute;sentera&raquo;, au sens litt&eacute;ral du mot, qui sera lui-m&ecirc;me, C&apos;est une effigie, une image de sa personne. Mais ils lie se pr&eacute;occupent pas de la faire ressemblante. Ils y pensent si peu, que la participation recherch&eacute;e s&apos;&eacute;tablit non pas entre l&apos;homme et son image, mais entre lui et l&apos;arbre dans l&apos;&eacute;corce duquel elle est taill&eacute;e. <br><font color="green">[This is instructive. The natives want to know if anything bad has happened to the friendly visitor who is now far from them, and cannot give them news. They compensate for this by establishing a participation between him and a symbol which "will represent him", in the literal sense of the word, which will be himself. It is an effigy, an image of his person. But they don&apos;t worry about making it look like him. They think so little about it, that the desired participation is established not between man and his image, but between him and the tree from which the bark is cut.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 234</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
